  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7036.86 sitting right at the max positive gamma strike of 7035 (17.6B), dealers are aggressively selling into this strength to hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with massive positive GEX walls clustered between 7000-7050 suggests dealers will continue fade any upside momentum while providing support on dips toward the flip level at 6872. The wall_break event combined with the -0.3% 1-min decline after a 2.4% 5-min rally indicates we're hitting the ceiling of this gamma pocket, with 7030-7035 acting as the primary resistance zone where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to get pushed back down from these highs due to heavy dealer selling pressure.",
